WEBVTT

00:13.570 --> 00:15.130
Mic test!

00:15.130 --> 00:17.920
Check! One, two! Check one, two, three!

00:19.150 --> 00:21.720
Wow! You actually fixed it.

00:21.720 --> 00:23.110
This is how I treat my patients.

00:23.110 --> 00:24.740
Music changes a lot of things.

00:24.740 --> 00:26.480
Can I choose a song?

00:26.480 --> 00:27.510
Sure.

01:19.000 --> 01:20.970
If I knew I'd die on foreign soil like this,

01:20.970 --> 01:22.050
I would've just enjoyed my life a little more,

01:22.050 --> 01:23.570
instead of competing for the professor position.

01:24.060 --> 01:27.090
I should spend more money on having fun.

01:29.680 --> 01:31.670
No.

01:32.090 --> 01:35.250
Saying something like that before dying is so lame.

01:41.130 --> 01:43.220
Shi Jin, are you on your way?

01:44.770 --> 01:47.180
Why are you not coming?

01:47.800 --> 01:50.240
I’m afraid I can’t wait for you coming.

01:51.789 --> 01:53.180
But

01:53.690 --> 01:55.110
if I die,

01:55.110 --> 01:57.220
I guess you're the first one who'll find me.

02:03.620 --> 02:06.130
If I'd known I'd die like this,

02:06.130 --> 02:10.970
I would've told you how I felt about you.

02:12.150 --> 02:15.060
A great guy kissed me.

02:15.940 --> 02:17.750
My heart was beating like crazy.

02:33.480 --> 02:35.740
Music really changes a lot of things.

02:38.020 --> 02:41.530
I guess I'm at the center of that change.

02:48.670 --> 02:49.610
I'm so embarrassed.

02:54.860 --> 02:56.710
Oh my! What the heck!

02:58.079 --> 02:59.100
How did you get here?

02:59.490 --> 03:00.330
Why are you here?

03:01.090 --> 03:02.430
I want to take advantage of this situation.

03:03.530 --> 03:04.980
Is it okay for you to use your skills

03:04.980 --> 03:06.270
of becoming a Special Forces soldier like this?

03:06.270 --> 03:07.260
For personal reasons?

03:07.260 --> 03:09.600
Because someone announced something personal on the air.

03:09.600 --> 03:13.070
We need doctors who go on air, and I'm one of them. ?

03:13.070 --> 03:14.930
Wow! I can't believe this!

03:14.930 --> 03:16.180
Why did you listen to my personal record?

03:16.180 --> 03:17.540
I didn't listen to it. I just heard it.

03:17.540 --> 03:18.980
You should've covered your ears.

03:18.980 --> 03:20.329
I find it is cute

03:22.010 --> 03:23.590
when you get angry like that.

03:24.120 --> 03:25.450
By the way, why are you running away?

03:26.320 --> 03:28.200
You were about to confess before you died,

03:29.100 --> 03:30.630
but now you're alive and you've changed your mind?

03:31.490 --> 03:33.430
Confess? I didn't confess anything.

03:33.430 --> 03:34.860
What I heard was your voice.

03:34.860 --> 03:35.840
It wasn't me.

03:35.840 --> 03:37.210
This phone is yours.

03:37.210 --> 03:38.579
It's not phone…

03:39.290 --> 03:40.640
Geez! Kang Mo Yeon! Calm down.

03:40.640 --> 03:42.290
Stop talking! Please!

03:42.470 --> 03:44.150
I'm so honored that I'm in your will.

03:44.150 --> 03:45.200
You should be.

03:46.280 --> 03:47.310
I'm not done yet.

03:47.910 --> 03:48.620
Hey! Look!

03:49.390 --> 03:50.270
I'm not buying it.

03:50.750 --> 03:51.710
Stop rejecting me.

03:51.710 --> 03:53.320
Do you know how many times you rejected me?

03:55.540 --> 03:57.920
I'm going to get your answer now.

03:58.730 --> 03:59.730
You can't run this time.

04:03.020 --> 04:04.010
I won't.

04:05.240 --> 04:06.400
I'll answer you,

04:07.260 --> 04:08.520
so can you let go?

04:10.540 --> 04:11.600
For real.

04:11.600 --> 04:12.580
For real?

04:24.850 --> 04:26.920
Flowers bloom in the midst of war.

04:27.370 --> 04:28.980
Romance blooms even during an earthquake.

04:29.900 --> 04:33.170
Here, people confess love, kiss each other

04:34.350 --> 04:36.530
and live their lives so intensely.

04:36.530 --> 04:38.460
Why don't we live more intensely?

04:38.460 --> 04:40.140
We could kiss each other out of working time.

04:40.680 --> 04:42.050
You're really funny.

04:42.680 --> 04:45.560
Don't you still realize that

04:45.560 --> 04:47.840
we should enjoy our lives while we can?

04:47.840 --> 04:49.050
Stop talking!

04:50.200 --> 04:53.460
Do you remember my will?

04:53.610 --> 04:55.350
Folder Bulbul. 1030.

04:55.350 --> 04:56.350
Delete it right away.

04:57.020 --> 04:58.409
How could you do it to an innocent bulbul?

04:58.409 --> 05:00.360
Does the bird know what's in it?

05:00.970 --> 05:02.470
Poor bulbul!

05:04.470 --> 05:06.020
Why are you worried about a bulbul?

05:09.850 --> 05:11.600
I was right, wasn't I?

05:14.870 --> 05:18.530
From now on, should we treat Dr. Kang as the boss's wife?

05:18.530 --> 05:22.010
She's not his wife. They're not married.

05:22.320 --> 05:24.160
Do it right! Don't be ridiculous!

05:26.250 --> 05:28.690
I don't like Dr. Kang.

05:29.380 --> 05:30.590
Why not?

05:30.940 --> 05:32.880
She's a big shot doctor and pretty.

05:32.880 --> 05:34.270
She's perfect.

05:34.270 --> 05:36.070
That's why I don't like her.

05:36.070 --> 05:37.500
Why would a rich and pretty doctor

05:37.540 --> 05:39.440
date a soldier?

05:39.659 --> 05:40.600
Out of charity?

05:41.900 --> 05:43.200
She's in an exotic land.

05:43.200 --> 05:45.740
You don't know when she's going to have a change of heart.

05:45.740 --> 05:47.430
What if she finds out what we really do?

05:47.740 --> 05:48.850
She may ask him to

05:48.850 --> 05:50.350
change his job,

05:50.350 --> 05:51.600
You know the drill.

05:56.100 --> 05:58.370
So frustrating.

06:01.820 --> 06:04.140
What does Sergeant Choi's wife do?

06:04.520 --> 06:06.120
Just like Dr. Kang,

06:06.120 --> 06:08.400
she's successful and really pretty.

06:08.400 --> 06:09.350
Right!

06:09.850 --> 06:10.950
What's wrong with him?

06:11.930 --> 06:14.450
By the way, he didn't give you 20 dollars.

06:16.220 --> 06:17.330
Unbelievable! Stop right there!

06:18.070 --> 06:18.800
Get him!

06:24.350 --> 06:26.100
Ms. Ha, can you make a list of

06:26.100 --> 06:27.890
the medicine that we need

06:27.890 --> 06:29.340
and send it to our hospital in Seoul?

06:29.500 --> 06:31.130
Let me get this straight.

06:31.130 --> 06:33.980
You confessed your love to Captain Yoo, right?

06:33.980 --> 06:34.980
Considering the circumstances,

06:34.980 --> 06:37.909
it's fair to say that Captain Yoo approached her first.

06:40.760 --> 06:42.010
Why don't you talk behind my back

06:42.010 --> 06:43.370
like other intelligent people do?

06:44.460 --> 06:46.520
Let's focus, okay?

06:47.180 --> 06:48.870
Those who are going back home tomorrow...

06:48.870 --> 06:50.350
Is this Day One for these two?

06:50.350 --> 06:51.409
Tomorrow is Day One.

06:51.960 --> 06:54.850
- No. They started today, so today is Day One. - Right.

06:55.140 --> 06:56.780
Do you really have to contribute?

06:58.440 --> 07:00.020
Those who go home on Day One...

07:04.690 --> 07:06.870
Why don't you all go home tomorrow? Huh?

07:21.310 --> 07:22.840
Let me check your blood pressure.

07:25.840 --> 07:26.690
Excuse me, Doc!

07:28.020 --> 07:29.860
Can I have another doctor, not him?

07:30.880 --> 07:31.920
Why?

07:31.920 --> 07:34.210
He's the one who found you first.

07:34.210 --> 07:35.820
I know.

07:36.730 --> 07:38.570
He keeps reminding me of that moment,

07:38.570 --> 07:39.650
and that makes me furious.

07:40.540 --> 07:42.180
His hands are shaky as well.

07:46.240 --> 07:48.070
Let me see.

07:48.070 --> 07:49.430
Who should I recommend?

07:49.430 --> 07:51.880
Albert Schweitzer. What about Schweitzer?

07:52.240 --> 07:53.340
He's not fluent in Korean.

07:53.930 --> 07:57.400
Or Jang Jun Hyeok? But he's dead.

07:57.860 --> 08:00.160
Too bad. We don't have another doctor.

08:03.150 --> 08:04.800
By the way, doctors aren't live TVs.

08:05.650 --> 08:09.000
You can't just change doctors like you change TV channels.

08:09.520 --> 08:11.120
If you want to get better, let him treat you.

08:12.770 --> 08:14.450
Take care of him, so he can get well.

08:18.270 --> 08:21.370
120, 80. Normal.

09:03.950 --> 09:05.120
What are you doing?

09:06.530 --> 09:07.390
I'm not doing anything.

09:07.390 --> 09:08.290
You did something, right?

09:09.180 --> 09:11.680
You look like you were avoiding people because you were embarrassed.

09:12.540 --> 09:13.900
Why don't you keep working?

09:13.900 --> 09:15.340
You're quite brave.

09:15.340 --> 09:16.530
You decided to date

09:16.530 --> 09:18.560
the leader of Alpha Team.

09:22.210 --> 09:24.710
Lieutenant Yoon. Let me ask you something.

09:25.130 --> 09:26.390
Go ahead,

09:26.840 --> 09:28.460
but no need to lower your voice

09:29.020 --> 09:31.150
This is my turf.

09:31.730 --> 09:37.010
Doesn't what your boyfriend does bother you at all?

09:38.020 --> 09:41.590
Aren't you worried he might get hurt or disappear?

09:42.800 --> 09:43.820
As far as I know,

09:44.970 --> 09:46.850
Sergeant Seo is also in a dangerous line of work

09:46.850 --> 09:47.780
like Captain Yoo.

09:49.090 --> 09:50.200
To be exact,

09:50.200 --> 09:51.950
during an emergency,

09:51.950 --> 09:54.180
they infiltrate enemy lines using various routes,

09:54.180 --> 09:55.400
such as by land, by sea, and by air engage

09:55.400 --> 09:56.680
in guerrilla warfare, work in espionage,

09:56.680 --> 09:57.700
collecting information, rescuing hostages,

09:57.700 --> 09:59.860
and destroy infrastructure

09:59.860 --> 10:01.520
while putting their lives at risk.

10:04.690 --> 10:06.830
But I'm more afraid of

10:07.590 --> 10:10.120
being away from him than what he does.

10:11.310 --> 10:12.840
I'm with him at the moment

10:12.840 --> 10:13.880
and I'm not afraid of anything at all.

10:14.640 --> 10:16.550
In other words, I have no fear.

10:17.750 --> 10:18.600
That's just me.

10:50.430 --> 10:51.490
Why so upset?

10:52.330 --> 10:53.840
I'm just lost in thought.

10:55.120 --> 10:57.240
Speaking of which, let me ask you one thing.

10:59.760 --> 11:02.040
You’ve never cared about what he does?

11:02.480 --> 11:04.410
Why are you doing this to me?

11:04.410 --> 11:06.250
Why don't you two talk it out?

11:07.360 --> 11:09.110
Kang Mo Yeon just asked me the same thing.

11:11.060 --> 11:13.290
How did you answer her?

11:13.290 --> 11:15.010
Ask her yourself.

11:15.010 --> 11:17.890
This is not an information war, but an all-out war.

11:17.890 --> 11:18.720
Look who's talking.

11:20.010 --> 11:21.050
What about you?

11:21.930 --> 11:23.700
I prefer hand-to-hand combat. en no one was around

11:26.160 --> 11:29.420
What's this? Whom are you going to throw it at?

11:29.620 --> 11:31.020
I’m searching for a target.

11:32.730 --> 11:33.740
Take it if you can.

11:34.390 --> 11:35.820
Don't do anything that you'll regret and come here.

11:35.820 --> 11:37.010
Why? You can't take it from me?

11:46.690 --> 11:48.540
That's why I told you to come here.

11:49.280 --> 11:50.900
You two lovebirds look good together.

11:51.850 --> 11:52.840
What's this about?

11:53.540 --> 11:55.150
Am I not allowed to flirt with a guy other than you?

11:55.150 --> 11:56.440
Are you still angry?

11:56.630 --> 11:58.190
What do you think?

11:58.190 --> 11:59.170
Did I ask you to do it

11:59.170 --> 12:01.210
every time after a meal?

12:01.210 --> 12:02.460
I asked you to do it when nobody can see us.

12:02.460 --> 12:03.960
Why you keep running away like that?

12:04.880 --> 12:06.940
Isn't it time for you to call roll?

12:12.220 --> 12:16.820
Right. That thing. That thing a man and a woman do.

12:18.160 --> 12:19.370
Not that.

12:20.600 --> 12:23.040
Holding hands. Hugging for a few minutes.

12:23.520 --> 12:26.630
That's all I want. Yet he won't even do that.

12:27.130 --> 12:28.760
He never holds my hands.

12:28.810 --> 12:30.570
He only grabs my arm or taps my shoulder.

12:31.800 --> 12:32.740
What a fool!

12:36.600 --> 12:39.170
He's your target. Throw the pebble at him.

12:43.160 --> 12:44.680
What a fool!

12:45.510 --> 12:47.790
Stop! I can take your rank badge of.

12:47.790 --> 12:51.080
Why? Because you can touch my shoulder?

12:52.450 --> 12:53.470
You're a man of principle.

12:55.600 --> 12:57.100
What a fool!

13:07.410 --> 13:10.510
One, two, three, four!

13:10.510 --> 13:12.850
It's so heartwarming to see them again.

13:13.880 --> 13:15.430
Our life seems to be back to normal.

13:16.360 --> 13:19.330
It's nice to see the muscular men running

13:19.330 --> 13:20.580
every day.

13:23.360 --> 13:24.980
It's like a symbol of peace.

13:26.360 --> 13:28.250
They're like a pigeon of peace.

13:32.180 --> 13:34.300
Don't you have a meeting at the UN Camp?

13:34.960 --> 13:36.640
Aren't you late for the meeting?

13:36.960 --> 13:38.290
I can be late.

13:40.550 --> 13:42.560
Captain Yoo! How are you?

13:42.920 --> 13:46.750
Two, three, four.

13:58.470 --> 13:59.870
That was too easy.

14:00.500 --> 14:03.220
Maybe kissing isn't the only thing they did.

14:04.040 --> 14:05.010
Ms. Choi.

14:06.020 --> 14:06.770
Yes?

14:10.630 --> 14:12.170
Do people really kiss each other during working hours?

14:13.400 --> 14:14.190
What?

14:24.220 --> 14:25.440
You scared me!

14:26.050 --> 14:27.530
Why are you here?

14:28.370 --> 14:29.610
How can you be here?

14:30.130 --> 14:31.590
I've been here all along.

14:36.180 --> 14:37.460
Did someone tease you?

14:37.460 --> 14:38.410
This is your fault!

14:40.750 --> 14:44.600
I'm busy. I have a meeting to go to. Excuse me.

14:45.180 --> 14:46.530
I have to go to the same meeting.

14:47.040 --> 14:48.780
You just found yourself a ride.

14:49.340 --> 14:50.230
I can go by myself.

14:50.230 --> 14:51.530
So you'll end up at a cliff edge?

14:51.930 --> 14:53.260
If that happens, I'll call you.

14:54.570 --> 14:56.060
Why do you keep running away?

14:57.470 --> 14:58.740
I confessed my feelings and you ran.

14:59.250 --> 15:01.170
You confessed your feelings in your will and ran.

15:01.170 --> 15:02.250
It wasn't my will.

15:02.290 --> 15:03.280
You said your heart was racing.

15:03.280 --> 15:04.620
It wasn't me.

15:06.440 --> 15:09.450
I'm not asking how you feel about me at the moment.

15:14.620 --> 15:17.010
Don't feel bad that I found out how you feel about me....

15:17.740 --> 15:21.520
Because I like you more than you like me.

15:25.430 --> 15:30.140
By the way, you look so pretty today.

15:31.660 --> 15:33.260
Please!

15:37.620 --> 15:39.010
See you at the front gate in 10 minutes.

16:00.890 --> 16:02.900
Which isn't logic that a speaker can use?

16:02.900 --> 16:06.270
One. He can explain the relationship between 20 million Koreans abroad.

16:06.270 --> 16:09.090
Two, to find a better country.

16:09.570 --> 16:11.180
Are you studying for the HSGEE?

16:11.640 --> 16:14.120
Yes, I guess I need a high school diploma.

16:14.910 --> 16:17.640
You're a nurse and you can perform acupuncture.

16:17.640 --> 16:19.120
Did you major in Oriental medicine as well?

16:19.500 --> 16:20.940
I didn't go to college.

16:20.940 --> 16:24.000
My father was an Oriental doctor, so I learned watching over his shoulders.

16:24.000 --> 16:26.580
Are you saying that you don't have a license?

16:28.620 --> 16:30.700
Then I don't want to do this anymore. Thank you.

16:30.700 --> 16:33.160
If you move suddenly, your mouth will be distorted.

16:33.370 --> 16:34.610
Okay.

16:37.640 --> 16:39.650
By the way, where are you from?

16:39.650 --> 16:41.940
Your accent is quite different from ours.

16:43.000 --> 16:44.050
I'm Kareiski (ethnic Korean).

16:44.780 --> 16:47.330
Kareiski? Kareiski?

16:48.120 --> 16:49.850
Where is it exactly?

16:49.850 --> 16:52.140
I think I heard it on a TV drama a long time ago.

16:52.140 --> 16:54.500
I've never met one before.

16:57.970 --> 16:59.070
How are you going to pass the exam?

17:02.300 --> 17:04.579
I thought it'd be very formal and serious,

17:04.579 --> 17:06.010
but everyone seems very nice.

17:06.460 --> 17:07.220
They face depressing incidents

17:07.220 --> 17:09.140
all the time.

17:09.140 --> 17:10.540
Humor is what keeps them going.

17:10.940 --> 17:12.790
Right.

17:14.240 --> 17:15.339
You do the same thing.

17:15.930 --> 17:17.670
When things are serious, you make jokes.

17:17.819 --> 17:19.810
When things are serious, why make things more serious by saying serious things?

17:24.220 --> 17:26.680
How do you feel about doing things that require sacrifice? time?

17:27.250 --> 17:28.480
Are you proud?

17:28.480 --> 17:30.030
I can't meet women.

17:31.340 --> 17:32.220
Right.

17:35.630 --> 17:36.580
Speaking of which,

17:37.770 --> 17:39.490
how many exes do you have?

17:41.130 --> 17:42.790
Why do men ask that question all the time?

17:42.790 --> 17:44.720
Who’s the guy asking the same question?

18:01.420 --> 18:02.200
What was that?

18:02.200 --> 18:05.230
I'm going to check it out. Don't move and stay here.

18:23.020 --> 18:24.250
What? What is it?

18:24.700 --> 18:27.440
If I'm right, it's a mine.

18:28.000 --> 18:29.120
What? A mine?

18:39.950 --> 18:42.480
Is it really a mine? Did we drive over a mine?

18:42.920 --> 18:44.100
Yes.

18:44.830 --> 18:46.590
I think those landmines were swept away

18:46.590 --> 18:47.970
during the earthquake.

18:48.250 --> 18:49.740
You shouldn't walk around by yourself.

18:51.840 --> 18:54.030
We're in the middle of a mine field.

18:54.870 --> 18:56.310
What should we do now?

18:59.480 --> 19:00.750
There's no reception on my phone.

19:05.800 --> 19:06.750
My walkie-talkie isn't working either.

19:07.650 --> 19:08.550
Give me your purse.

19:13.560 --> 19:14.800
What for?

19:14.800 --> 19:16.990
Don't we have to wait until a rescue team gets here?

19:19.440 --> 19:20.290
Can you hold onto these?

19:24.320 --> 19:25.400
Let's go.

19:30.760 --> 19:32.550
We're going to get out of here.

19:33.270 --> 19:34.660
There are mines everywhere. How?

19:35.030 --> 19:36.610
Follow my footsteps.

19:37.930 --> 19:40.630
I won't let you die. Don't worry.

19:51.290 --> 19:54.030
What happens if you step on a mine?

19:56.160 --> 19:57.300
You're done.

19:58.440 --> 20:00.890
Unlike movies, if you step on it, it goes off.

20:01.850 --> 20:05.380
Okay. Here.

20:05.380 --> 20:08.400
Take bigger steps. Can you do it?

20:08.890 --> 20:09.940
Hold my hand.

20:17.470 --> 20:18.330
Good job.

20:19.080 --> 20:19.860
All.

20:21.850 --> 20:22.520
Hang in there.

20:22.830 --> 20:23.650
You too.

20:31.090 --> 20:32.290
Is that a mine?

20:32.290 --> 20:36.670
Yes. It's an M16A1 anti-personnel mine.

20:37.010 --> 20:38.750
Can you give me the flags in your purse?

20:41.050 --> 20:41.830
Here.

20:45.230 --> 20:46.250
The only way to beat landmines

20:46.250 --> 20:48.460
is to take it slow.

20:49.680 --> 20:53.340
Take it easy while appreciating my sexy back.

20:55.160 --> 20:56.430
This is the moment

20:57.170 --> 20:58.710
when you need silly jokes.

21:02.200 --> 21:03.690
"Take it easy" is the joke part.

21:04.350 --> 21:05.410
I'm serious about the other part.

21:05.920 --> 21:07.220
Come on!

21:46.880 --> 21:47.970
Good.

21:49.010 --> 21:50.140
You did an excellent job.

21:51.020 --> 21:52.610
Unbelievable!

21:52.610 --> 21:54.560
Why do I keep risking my life every day?

21:55.390 --> 21:56.420
I've already destroyed two cars.

21:56.990 --> 22:00.720
I wanted to shoot a melodrama with you

22:01.390 --> 22:02.460
but we ended up in a blockbuster.

22:03.770 --> 22:05.130
Since you destroyed two cars,

22:05.320 --> 22:06.510
why don't I destroy a lipstick?

22:07.680 --> 22:10.500
Do you carry lipstick with you?

22:32.470 --> 22:34.200
Done. Let's go.

22:34.780 --> 22:35.780
Wait a minute.

22:43.520 --> 22:45.160
For those who don't speak English.

22:54.200 --> 22:55.560
I'm not complaining or anything.

22:56.440 --> 22:59.050
I just want to get some facts straight.

22:59.910 --> 23:02.540
Should we just keep walking like this?

23:03.250 --> 23:04.180
For now.

23:05.210 --> 23:06.770
It took about 40 minutes

23:06.770 --> 23:08.530
at 60 kilograms per hour.

23:09.270 --> 23:10.370
So it’s about 40 kilograms.

23:11.470 --> 23:12.920
At the speed of Special Forces,

23:12.920 --> 23:14.360
we would arrive at the camp by evening.

23:15.030 --> 23:16.860
But with you, We'll get there tomorrow morning.

23:19.940 --> 23:22.410
Do you want to hold hands?

23:23.280 --> 23:23.920
No.

23:23.920 --> 23:24.970
Even though I'm the guy

23:24.970 --> 23:25.960
in your will?

23:25.960 --> 23:27.100
It wasn't me.

23:28.970 --> 23:30.820
You treat me like that again after I saved you.

23:31.370 --> 23:32.510
What?

23:33.320 --> 23:35.540
You're completely different before and after you face a crisis.

23:37.810 --> 23:40.400
Actually, you're different in the morning and in the afternoon.

23:40.400 --> 23:41.620
Me?

23:41.620 --> 23:43.870
How am I different in the morning and afternoon?

23:43.870 --> 23:47.500
You're really pretty in the morning and amazingly pretty in the afternoon.

23:50.030 --> 23:51.120
Be honest with me.

23:51.970 --> 23:53.830
You've dated a truckload of women, right?

23:53.830 --> 23:55.810
Why do women ask something like this?

23:56.360 --> 23:57.790
If I say yes, you get angry.

23:58.210 --> 24:00.470
If I say no, you won't trust me.

24:01.400 --> 24:03.560
Who got angry and who didn't trust you? Huh?

24:04.980 --> 24:06.640
A truck!

24:07.850 --> 24:10.000
Was the truck about that size?

24:12.100 --> 24:14.650
Hey! Over here! Please!

24:23.250 --> 24:25.270
I don't think the locals appreciate your beauty.

24:25.270 --> 24:26.310
What?

24:27.750 --> 24:28.910
Look! Here comes another car!

24:29.400 --> 24:30.270
Do you want a car?

24:30.660 --> 24:32.030
Should I hijack it? With this gun?

24:32.850 --> 24:34.340
Stay out of it. Over here!

24:35.700 --> 24:38.670
Hey! Help us! Over here!

24:39.330 --> 24:43.330
Stop! Stop! Stop!

24:46.630 --> 24:48.030
Good idea. Let's hijack it.

24:57.480 --> 25:01.020
I guess farmers are nice everywhere in the world.

25:02.190 --> 25:04.180
You're different before and after you got on the truck.

25:05.760 --> 25:07.930
Thank you for saving me again.

25:08.310 --> 25:10.380
I felt good

25:10.380 --> 25:11.490
because you had my back earlier.

25:11.490 --> 25:13.090
I'll have a good life.

25:14.060 --> 25:15.290
With another guy?

25:17.290 --> 25:17.860
Don't have a good life oes.

25:17.860 --> 25:18.970
with another guy.

25:23.390 --> 25:25.100
You asked Myung Joo

25:25.560 --> 25:27.580
if what her boyfriend does bothers her?

25:28.070 --> 25:29.770
She a tattletale or something?

25:30.090 --> 25:32.060
She asked me to get the answer from you.

25:34.260 --> 25:35.500
What did Myung Joo say?

25:37.790 --> 25:39.410
She said

25:39.930 --> 25:42.220
she'd be more afraid to be away

25:42.220 --> 25:44.370
from Sergeant Seo than what he actually does.

25:45.370 --> 25:46.320
What about us?

25:47.810 --> 25:49.350
Are we

25:50.410 --> 25:53.280
going to be away from each other?

25:55.760 --> 25:57.570
Is your name?

25:58.220 --> 25:59.500
on the passenger list to Korea?

26:01.400 --> 26:02.310
No.

26:04.910 --> 26:05.770
No?

26:05.770 --> 26:08.580
No. I'm not going home.

26:09.160 --> 26:10.170
Why not?

26:11.610 --> 26:12.750
I don't think it's me.

26:12.750 --> 26:14.700
It is you.

26:15.420 --> 26:17.200
I'm not going home because of you.

26:17.980 --> 26:20.840
Because I want to be with you

26:20.840 --> 26:22.130
a little longer.

26:24.940 --> 26:26.490
There! I just said it.

26:27.900 --> 26:28.900
Do you want me to apologize?

26:29.540 --> 26:31.140
How do you expect me to react to that?

27:37.680 --> 27:39.030
You had a long day today.

27:39.950 --> 27:42.020
I need to start roll call.

27:42.910 --> 27:44.170
You did a great job today.

27:44.170 --> 27:46.180
I need to get ready for my rounds.

27:46.570 --> 27:48.520
Ma'am!

28:04.260 --> 28:06.010
She must feel so awkward.

28:06.010 --> 28:07.660
He must've been really happy.

28:08.270 --> 28:09.680
I want to clean the hay off of her.

28:10.000 --> 28:11.640
I want to go slap him.

28:15.110 --> 28:15.950
What?

28:16.600 --> 28:17.710
I really want to slap you.

28:53.770 --> 28:55.170
Here.

28:58.930 --> 29:00.110
It's in here.

29:03.900 --> 29:05.070
Move!

29:16.200 --> 29:21.650
I barely found it but as you can see, the lock was broken.

29:21.650 --> 29:23.540
I had no choice

29:24.110 --> 29:30.400
but to bring the whole thing. So you guys should open it.

29:35.330 --> 29:36.170
But

29:36.880 --> 29:40.790
you're 27 hours and 15 minutes late.

29:46.880 --> 29:48.560
Please don't kill me.

29:49.790 --> 29:52.640
It was the earthquake.

29:52.640 --> 29:54.220
Do you know what a battlefield and

29:54.220 --> 29:56.280
a disaster scene have in common?

29:57.950 --> 30:00.010
No one cares or

30:01.710 --> 30:04.110
even notices the corpses.

30:04.980 --> 30:08.340
Please. Please let me go. I'll do anything. Everything.

30:08.340 --> 30:10.150
No, no.

30:11.650 --> 30:13.580
You don't have to do everything.

30:15.840 --> 30:22.250
Just do what I tell you. Okay?

30:22.250 --> 30:27.210
Okay! Sure! No problem! Yes! Yes!

30:43.680 --> 30:46.320
What do you mean there are no diamonds?

30:47.050 --> 30:50.180
I think he fooled us. Look, I'll go and get him...

30:50.650 --> 30:55.330
Think about it. You know what territory he's already in?

31:09.040 --> 31:10.750
I'm really sick.

31:12.160 --> 31:17.370
I can't even keep my head steady.

31:17.370 --> 31:19.230
I'm in a great deal of pain.

31:19.230 --> 31:20.210
What's going on?

31:21.110 --> 31:23.070
He was perfectly fine until yesterday

31:23.070 --> 31:24.850
but now he's in a great deal of pain.

31:24.850 --> 31:26.330
I think he's going to pass away tomorrow.

31:26.330 --> 31:27.890
Aftereffects can be dangerous as well.

31:28.250 --> 31:30.780
This wasn't a simple car accident.

31:30.780 --> 31:33.050
It was a huge earthquake

31:33.050 --> 31:35.190
and I'm the victim of an assault.

31:35.190 --> 31:36.980
Why don't you keep it down?

31:37.680 --> 31:38.570
X-ray and motor

31:38.570 --> 31:40.040
response test results are okay.

31:42.050 --> 31:43.780
In the era of LTE like these days,

31:43.780 --> 31:45.770
you'd tie a letter around a pigeon's ankle?

31:46.110 --> 31:49.670
What can you find out with an X-ray?

31:50.070 --> 31:51.410
I'm going to take an MRI scan

31:51.410 --> 31:53.680
at a big hospital in Seoul.

31:53.680 --> 31:56.810
I want a ticket on the plane taking your employees back home tomorrow.

31:56.810 --> 31:58.400
I told you.

31:58.400 --> 32:00.300
We have no extra seats.

32:00.440 --> 32:02.530
Are you here to get a plane ticket?

32:02.530 --> 32:04.230
At Medical Zone?

32:04.230 --> 32:05.350
Are you out of your mind?

32:05.350 --> 32:07.400
How dare you look at me like that?

32:09.380 --> 32:10.950
Make a seat.

32:10.950 --> 32:12.300
It's me. Jin Yeong Su.

32:12.300 --> 32:13.830
And you!

32:13.830 --> 32:15.860
Do you think you're better than me

32:15.860 --> 32:18.070
because you're wearing a military uniform?

32:18.520 --> 32:20.160
Can we talk outside in private?

32:20.490 --> 32:21.270
Come on!

32:21.270 --> 32:22.000
I'll take care of him.

32:22.000 --> 32:24.340
Let go! Hey! Let go of me!

32:24.340 --> 32:25.660
Eyes down!

32:26.020 --> 32:27.420
Let go! I said let go!

32:27.420 --> 32:29.390
Let go of me, you jerk!

32:29.390 --> 32:31.050
Hey! Let go!

32:39.960 --> 32:42.950
Did you just hit me? You jerk!

32:44.190 --> 32:46.200
Do you want to become a patient?

32:46.530 --> 32:49.550
Where do you want me to break?

32:52.630 --> 32:53.950
Should I break this?

32:55.580 --> 32:56.950
What about living as a leftie?

32:56.950 --> 32:58.240
That could be arranged.

33:00.150 --> 33:03.150
What about the temple here? Tell me.

33:03.840 --> 33:05.010
I can put you in a hospital

33:05.010 --> 33:06.220
for the rest of your life.

33:06.740 --> 33:08.270
That’s not I mean.

33:08.810 --> 33:12.400
I was a little frustrated and was acting rude.

33:12.400 --> 33:13.710
I admit my mistake.

33:13.710 --> 33:15.160
Get out of here before I hurt you.

33:15.160 --> 33:16.280
You know where the entrance is.

33:16.280 --> 33:19.230
You have five seconds. One, two, three...

33:19.230 --> 33:21.680
Hold on! Hold on a minute!

33:23.820 --> 33:29.760
I don't usually make mistakes that often. I'm sorry.

33:31.370 --> 33:36.710
Hey, Doctor! Can you tell them that I feel sorry about what happened?

33:37.830 --> 33:40.780
Do you want a seat on the plane?

33:41.210 --> 33:42.090
What?

33:46.640 --> 33:47.630
Stay in touch.

33:47.630 --> 33:48.760
Bye.

33:48.760 --> 33:50.170
I'll see you later. Take care.

34:16.370 --> 34:19.570
By the way, where is Chi Hoon?

34:21.969 --> 34:23.690
Did that jerk take his seat from him?

34:25.210 --> 34:26.840
They need to leave now to catch the plane.

34:30.010 --> 34:30.929
Did you find him?

34:30.929 --> 34:33.909
No. I can't find him anywhere.

34:34.690 --> 34:35.710
You should leave now.

34:35.920 --> 34:37.900
Take care and call me when you get there.

34:38.310 --> 34:40.120
Yes. I'll call you.

34:40.810 --> 34:41.940
Take good care of yourselves.

34:41.940 --> 34:44.480
- Have a safe trip. - Take care.

34:55.370 --> 34:57.760
Did something happen to Dr. Lee?

34:58.260 --> 35:01.030
Right? He's been acting weird lately.

35:01.430 --> 35:03.430
He's been wearing the same shoes for three days.

35:03.430 --> 35:04.660
He doesn't care about his looks.

35:07.380 --> 35:09.370
You jerk! What are you doing here?

35:09.840 --> 35:11.720
Where have you been hiding all day long?

35:13.170 --> 35:14.880
I checked this place earlier..

35:17.730 --> 35:20.690
Has everyone left?

35:21.250 --> 35:22.720
All of them have left,

35:22.720 --> 35:25.800
but why are you still here?

35:27.770 --> 35:30.840
I know how you feel.

35:30.840 --> 35:32.310
Dr. Jang has gained a lot of weight,

35:32.310 --> 35:34.020
even for a pregnant woman.

35:34.020 --> 35:37.980
I guess you don't find her as attractive as before.

35:38.860 --> 35:40.220
But still, you can't do this to her.

35:40.220 --> 35:41.430
If you want to stay away from home,

35:41.430 --> 35:43.200
spend some time in the cities

35:43.200 --> 35:45.090
near your home.

35:45.090 --> 35:47.810
Don't you think Uruk, on the opposite side of the world,

35:47.810 --> 35:48.990
is a little too far away?

35:51.990 --> 35:54.830
Yes. It is too far.

35:57.330 --> 35:58.780
That's why I couldn't leave.

36:00.560 --> 36:03.470
If I run too far away,

36:05.470 --> 36:06.940
I'm not a real doctor.

36:08.800 --> 36:11.850
Chi Hoon, let me ask you this for the last time.

36:15.410 --> 36:18.050
What happened between you and Kang Min Jae? What is it? I can help.

36:20.770 --> 36:22.380
Later.

36:24.450 --> 36:28.250
Getting help from you is like running away in a way.

36:30.520 --> 36:33.490
I'll try to figure it out on my own.

36:35.310 --> 36:36.750
If it doesn't work...

36:41.020 --> 36:42.750
I'll ask you for help.

37:13.940 --> 37:14.980
Let’s go.

37:24.070 --> 37:25.300
May I help you?

37:26.970 --> 37:29.260
No! No! Go!

37:31.000 --> 37:34.870
The plane left, but he didn't show up.

37:35.570 --> 37:37.970
I think he took off after suspecting us.

37:38.750 --> 37:42.500
But we set some traps with the police chief.

37:45.790 --> 37:48.330
He'll do anything to get out of this country.

37:48.330 --> 37:51.010
I'm going to tear him to pieces when I see him next.

37:51.800 --> 37:53.730
Prepare a rose instead of a gun

37:53.730 --> 37:55.580
to Colonel Aman's delivery.

37:56.190 --> 37:58.380
The red rose I chose previously.

37:58.700 --> 37:59.570
Yes, sir!

37:59.900 --> 38:00.960
Let's go!

39:17.510 --> 39:19.140
Are you going for the target's head?

39:19.980 --> 39:24.290
I'm going for her heart. The target is too pretty.

39:29.980 --> 39:32.180
I've finished the gun inspection and found no problems.

39:36.230 --> 39:37.830
I've checked my gun and there are no problems.

39:38.010 --> 39:40.570
Your gun has no problems, but you seem to have one.

39:40.570 --> 39:42.160
I don't.

39:42.780 --> 39:45.300
I won't accept any more questions.

39:45.300 --> 39:47.280
This is Harry Potter. Wolf, do you copy?

39:50.340 --> 39:51.990
This is Wolf. What's the problem?

39:51.990 --> 39:54.440
Yellow Tiger's visiting our unit tomorrow afternoon.

39:57.990 --> 39:59.690
Who's Yellow Tiger?

40:00.210 --> 40:01.160
You don't know?

40:01.160 --> 40:02.530
I don't.

40:03.670 --> 40:06.560
Yellow Tiger is Commander Yoon's call sign.

40:08.210 --> 40:09.880
You mean my dad?

40:11.930 --> 40:15.110
Tomorrow afternoon, the commander of the Special Warfare Command

40:15.110 --> 40:18.550
who came from Korea will be visiting us.

40:18.550 --> 40:19.940
Ah.

40:20.380 --> 40:21.460
Don't sigh.

40:22.290 --> 40:25.370
I'm not going to overreact

40:25.370 --> 40:26.820
like those other captains

40:26.820 --> 40:29.280
simply because a three-star general's coming.

40:29.280 --> 40:31.990
Oh.

40:31.990 --> 40:33.420
Like we always do,

40:33.420 --> 40:37.180
we'll cut the grass near the drill ground.

40:37.180 --> 40:39.380
Like we do all the time,

40:39.380 --> 40:43.310
we'll polish the sinks until they shine using toothpaste.

40:43.310 --> 40:46.520
Don't overdo it.

40:46.520 --> 40:49.860
Clean the drains and reorganize Storehouse One and Three.

40:50.260 --> 40:53.300
Like we always do.

40:54.420 --> 40:55.510
Do you understand?

41:12.890 --> 41:14.000
They're doing what they usually do.

41:16.270 --> 41:17.090
Sir!

41:18.240 --> 41:21.690
The Commander has a meeting with the UN Chief of the General Staff,

41:21.690 --> 41:23.420
so he cancelled his visit.

41:23.420 --> 41:24.250
Cancelled?

41:25.260 --> 41:29.020
We're working as usual like this.

41:29.550 --> 41:31.220
Instead, Commander Yoon asked you to come see him

41:31.220 --> 41:32.970
with Dr. Kang, the leader of the medical team.

41:33.670 --> 41:35.490
Sergeant Seo and Lieutenant Yoon are getting ready as well.

41:48.110 --> 41:50.000
You don't have to worry about me.

41:51.220 --> 41:53.840
I won't. Why would I?

41:55.260 --> 41:58.410
How should I address Myung Joo's father?

42:01.430 --> 42:02.390
Uncle?

42:11.360 --> 42:12.600
Attention!

42:13.250 --> 42:15.450
Salute the Commander!

42:15.450 --> 42:17.430
Sir.

42:30.800 --> 42:31.890
At ease!

42:32.630 --> 42:33.470
Thank you for your good work.

42:35.300 --> 42:37.670
Lieutenant Colonel Park Byung Soo!

42:37.970 --> 42:39.710
Colonel Kim Jong Ho!

42:53.110 --> 42:55.740
Division Commander. Before you start the briefing,

42:55.740 --> 42:58.940
can I use your office for half an hour?

42:58.940 --> 43:00.310
Yes, sir!

43:02.360 --> 43:04.380
Yoo Shi Jin, Seo Dae Young, Yoon Myung Joo

43:06.100 --> 43:08.460
and Dr. Kang. Can I see you for a minute?

43:15.670 --> 43:16.440
Have a seat!

43:16.440 --> 43:17.090
Thank you.

43:18.240 --> 43:19.120
I'm okay.

43:27.510 --> 43:30.400
Dr. Kang Mo Yeon, why didn't you become a soldier?

43:30.910 --> 43:31.590
Pardon?

43:31.590 --> 43:33.290
I heard about what you've done.

43:33.630 --> 43:35.980
The operation on the president of the Arab League.

43:37.530 --> 43:40.740
You have the courage to become a good soldier.

43:40.740 --> 43:41.540
It’s so pity.

43:41.880 --> 43:43.490
I'm flattered,

43:43.490 --> 43:45.680
but I can't get up in the morning.

43:46.310 --> 43:48.160
That's why you're so beautiful.

43:49.660 --> 43:51.080
Anyway,

43:51.080 --> 43:53.710
what you did ended up benefitting our nation.

43:53.710 --> 43:55.160
I wanted to show my appreciation.

43:55.650 --> 43:56.840
We'll see each other again.

43:56.840 --> 43:59.030
This is what I wanted to tell you.

44:00.900 --> 44:02.790
If you'll excuse me.

44:13.170 --> 44:15.040
I heard that you did a good job rescuing people after the earthquake.

44:15.040 --> 44:16.260
God job.

44:16.920 --> 44:18.730
Did any of you get hurt?

44:19.020 --> 44:20.050
No, sir!

44:21.100 --> 44:22.150
Good.

44:23.480 --> 44:26.220
From now on,

44:27.260 --> 44:29.310
I'm going to talk to you as Myung Joo's father.

44:30.500 --> 44:31.390
Yoo Shi Jin, you first.

44:33.090 --> 44:35.210
Yes, sir!

44:36.200 --> 44:39.070
Yoo Shi Jin,

44:39.070 --> 44:40.260
are you my ally or enemy?

44:40.760 --> 44:42.230
Pick your side.

44:43.340 --> 44:46.660
You're not at all attracted to my daughter?

44:46.660 --> 44:47.860
Dad.

44:53.360 --> 44:55.290
She's one of my favorite fellow soldiers.

44:55.610 --> 44:59.560
However, for the seven years I've known her,

44:59.910 --> 45:01.450
I've never thought of her in that way.

45:05.780 --> 45:07.090
That's disappointing.

45:11.090 --> 45:12.980
Okay. You can leave.

45:18.460 --> 45:19.530
That didn't take long.

45:20.130 --> 45:21.790
I thought you'd be talking about something serious.

45:23.010 --> 45:24.170
We did

45:24.970 --> 45:26.360
and he kicked me out right away.

45:26.800 --> 45:27.690
From the army?

45:27.690 --> 45:30.020
No. From his radar.

45:31.270 --> 45:33.960
As of today, he officially fired me as his future son-in-law candidate.

45:35.120 --> 45:36.530
That means...

45:36.530 --> 45:39.240
Yes, I'm now officially unattached.

45:41.150 --> 45:42.830
Are you okay with a guy with a history like me?

45:47.780 --> 45:52.230
What's going to happen to Lieutenant Yoon and Sergeant Seo from now on?

45:52.650 --> 45:53.770
I don't know.

45:54.700 --> 45:57.600
Sergeant Seo always ends up with a tough decision.

46:10.790 --> 46:11.850
What?

46:12.860 --> 46:15.290
Are you still happy to see Seo Dae Young?

46:15.950 --> 46:17.120
Yes, sir!

46:19.760 --> 46:21.090
Seo Dae Young,

46:21.530 --> 46:22.760
do you feel the same way?

46:24.120 --> 46:26.760
Ask me. Why do you bother him?

46:26.760 --> 46:27.970
Yes, sir!

46:31.700 --> 46:35.690
I thought we were on the same page.

46:37.500 --> 46:39.020
I thought

46:39.020 --> 46:41.120
you'd lose this fight for Myung Joo.

46:43.280 --> 46:46.700
Seo Dae Young. Answer me!

46:47.240 --> 46:49.210
My answer is...

46:49.210 --> 46:51.550
I don't care what he said before.

46:51.790 --> 46:53.290
I won't leave him, no matter what.

47:08.910 --> 47:12.450
I'm going to hold this hand.

47:15.880 --> 47:18.660
Do you think you're good enough to hold that hand?

47:18.660 --> 47:19.730
If you send me away,

47:19.730 --> 47:20.470
I'll go

47:20.470 --> 47:21.750
wherever it is,

47:22.720 --> 47:24.610
but I won't let this hand go.

47:25.970 --> 47:28.540
Yoon Myung Joo! Leave us.

47:28.540 --> 47:32.020
No. I'm going to stay here.

47:32.020 --> 47:33.150
Didn't I tell you earlier?

47:34.540 --> 47:36.480
Don’t worry.

47:45.650 --> 47:47.250
For 30 years of serving as a soldier,

47:47.250 --> 47:49.990
there were two things I wanted to achieve.

47:50.810 --> 47:52.810
First, to become an honorable commander.

47:52.810 --> 47:54.990
Second, to earn respect from my daughter.

47:58.670 --> 48:03.740
However, I failed to get either of them.

48:05.150 --> 48:08.240
My orders to you were all unjust

48:09.440 --> 48:11.570
and my daughter doesn't respect me.

48:13.360 --> 48:14.230
However,

48:15.930 --> 48:17.330
I know what you really want.

48:17.330 --> 48:19.150
So I'm going to tell you what I really want.

48:19.980 --> 48:25.160
Let's cut to the chase. You can go out with Myung Joo.

48:26.090 --> 48:29.930
Of course I'm thinking about you two getting married.

48:31.450 --> 48:32.990
Are you serious?

48:35.450 --> 48:36.700
I'm serious.

48:41.880 --> 48:46.090
However, I don't want a sergeant as a son-in-law.

48:47.160 --> 48:48.500
You need to leave the army.

48:50.000 --> 48:54.300
I want you to find a job at my family company.

48:56.080 --> 48:57.420
I'll find a position

48:57.420 --> 48:58.940
at one of my family businesses,

48:58.940 --> 49:00.850
so you can start over.

49:02.590 --> 49:04.910
Think about it until you finish your mission here

49:05.620 --> 49:08.800
and decide before you go back to Korea.

49:09.470 --> 49:11.390
If you're going to let her go

49:12.690 --> 49:15.150
or become a man who's suitable for her.

49:37.210 --> 49:38.190
What are you thinking?

49:41.010 --> 49:42.230
About Lieutenant Yoon and you.

49:44.060 --> 49:45.440
Myung Joo and I?

49:46.220 --> 49:49.780
Yes. I can't get my head around it.

49:50.580 --> 49:52.220
Why didn't you go out with Myung Joo?

49:52.870 --> 49:55.820
She's young, went to a fine school, has a rich family, and has a nice fugure.

49:56.170 --> 49:58.310
I can't find anything wrong with her.

50:01.050 --> 50:02.800
Being pretty and having rich parents don't mean anything to me.

50:05.090 --> 50:06.510
You think Myung Joo is pretty.

50:07.430 --> 50:08.790
I never said anything about being pretty.

50:10.750 --> 50:12.030
Are you jealous?

50:13.290 --> 50:14.650
Come here and hold this.

50:24.950 --> 50:25.960
Why change the subject?

50:26.700 --> 50:27.860
If you think she's pretty, why didn't you date her?

50:29.680 --> 50:31.360
Why do you think she's pretty?

50:36.430 --> 50:37.340
What are you doing?

50:37.340 --> 50:38.510
Shut you up

50:39.020 --> 50:40.750
in way of an adult.

50:40.750 --> 50:41.990
Keep talking.

50:42.640 --> 50:43.810
Go away!

50:53.240 --> 50:54.850
When is it going to be done?

50:56.840 --> 50:59.720
It's already done.

51:01.050 --> 51:01.940
I'll go pay.

51:10.710 --> 51:13.090
Get him! Catch that thief!

51:13.090 --> 51:14.670
You asshole.

51:19.070 --> 51:21.370
Let's put this aside for now.

51:21.370 --> 51:22.500
What's going on?

51:24.610 --> 51:25.790
It's okay.

51:27.370 --> 51:29.520
I think he stole the medicine since he's sick.

51:30.960 --> 51:32.240
Let's take him to the Medical Zone.

51:32.800 --> 51:35.190
No, we need to go to where he lives.

51:36.210 --> 51:38.270
High fever, spots, and papules.

51:38.270 --> 51:39.190
If I'm correct,

51:39.190 --> 51:40.870
he's got the measles.

51:40.870 --> 51:41.860
It's contagious.

51:42.830 --> 51:44.650
We have to do something before it spreads.

51:45.340 --> 51:47.870
No way! For real?

51:48.240 --> 51:49.660
If you want to back down, now's the time.

51:50.000 --> 51:51.160
Now or never.

51:51.460 --> 51:54.210
Really? You're not joking, right?

51:55.330 --> 51:57.550
Did he really say that we could date?

52:00.410 --> 52:01.280
Yes, ma'am.

52:02.850 --> 52:04.480
Sergeant Seo Dae Young

52:04.480 --> 52:06.780
was ordered to date you.

52:06.780 --> 52:09.020
This is official, ma'am!

52:13.010 --> 52:15.240
Why? What's this? I can't believe it!

52:17.830 --> 52:18.690
Does he have cancer?

52:19.830 --> 52:21.670
Is he terminally ill or something?

52:22.270 --> 52:23.230
I should call him.

52:24.030 --> 52:25.380
I can tell if he means it or not

52:25.380 --> 52:28.640
when I hear his voice. Bye.

52:35.830 --> 52:37.010
Right.

53:16.090 --> 53:18.330
This is Big Boss. We have arrived at the village.

53:19.390 --> 53:22.010
Can you check the GPS for our current location?

53:22.310 --> 53:24.390
This is Snoopy! This is Snoopy!

53:36.770 --> 53:37.810
Sir.

53:39.850 --> 53:42.070
I checked the GPS coordinates before the radio was cut off.

53:42.070 --> 53:43.430
It’s weird.

53:43.430 --> 53:44.610
There's no village

53:44.610 --> 53:46.100
at those coordinates.

53:46.760 --> 53:47.810
Really?

53:47.810 --> 53:49.450
You know that Peacemaker doctor.

53:49.720 --> 53:50.830
Contact him as soon as possible.

53:51.310 --> 53:52.150
Yes, sir!

53:59.590 --> 54:01.530
How long have they been sick?

54:07.420 --> 54:14.700
These children. Since when were they sick?

54:17.560 --> 54:18.820
I don't think they understand you.

54:19.590 --> 54:21.020
This is measles. What should we do?

54:22.000 --> 54:23.050
We have to collect everyone

54:23.050 --> 54:24.230
and test them.

54:25.560 --> 54:29.830
We get no food for three days if we speak to strangers.

54:29.830 --> 54:31.980
Thank god! She can speak English.

54:36.460 --> 54:38.770
Is it okay for you to speak to us?

54:38.770 --> 54:41.120
It doesn't matter to me anymore.

54:41.120 --> 54:43.580
Can you bring all the children together?

54:43.580 --> 54:45.960
The kids here have measles

54:45.960 --> 54:48.800
and it's a very serious viral disease.

54:48.800 --> 54:50.790
If they don't get treated now,

54:50.790 --> 54:53.900
70 percent will die or become disabled.

54:53.900 --> 54:55.970
It's better to die now

54:55.970 --> 54:57.240
than to live here.

54:58.440 --> 55:00.660
The boys here become a gang

55:00.660 --> 55:03.590
and the girls are sold to a pimp when they grow up.

55:04.320 --> 55:05.980
Today is my turn.

55:13.020 --> 55:14.390
I will cooperate

55:14.390 --> 55:18.080
but under one condition. Get me out of here.

55:21.030 --> 55:21.720
This place is...

55:21.720 --> 55:22.480
What is it?

55:24.110 --> 55:25.200
It's a ghost village.

55:25.840 --> 55:27.710
War orphans are gathered there.

55:27.710 --> 55:29.020
The local gang is in charge of this village.

55:29.550 --> 55:30.570
Not for taking care of them.

55:30.570 --> 55:31.290
They lock them up

55:31.290 --> 55:33.330
for human trafficking.

55:38.590 --> 55:39.520
A ghost village?

55:40.210 --> 55:41.310
Some gangs.

55:41.310 --> 55:44.070
trade the entire village including the orphans.

55:44.370 --> 55:47.110
They call it a ghost village because they move a lot.

55:55.360 --> 55:56.350
Hold on!

55:57.670 --> 55:58.990
You need to hurry.

55:58.990 --> 56:00.330
The landlord has just come back.

56:28.980 --> 56:30.400
Are you their guardian?

56:32.700 --> 56:34.590
I'm a doctor from Korea.

56:34.590 --> 56:37.030
Some children here have measles.

56:37.400 --> 56:38.150
Can I take them

56:38.150 --> 56:39.320
to the field hospital?

56:39.320 --> 56:42.380
You're too beautiful to be doing something good like this.

56:46.300 --> 56:47.320
Stay behind me.

56:48.170 --> 56:49.610
It's good to see you again, Captain.

56:53.340 --> 56:56.780
What a coincidence to see you in a place like this!

56:59.660 --> 57:01.100
Do you know him?

57:02.230 --> 57:03.200
Who is he?

57:06.110 --> 57:07.210
Private Ryan.

57:32.270 --> 57:34.730
I think I have the advantage this time, Big Boss.

57:51.190 --> 57:52.220
Boss!

57:54.370 --> 57:56.800
Hurry up! Let's leave now!

57:56.800 --> 57:57.990
It's our last chance.

58:00.560 --> 58:01.920
Please don't move!

58:01.920 --> 58:03.860
Hey, Doctor! Do something!

58:03.860 --> 58:05.990
No, don't!

58:05.990 --> 58:08.020
Just kill him! Let him die!

58:09.830 --> 58:11.620
Doctor, what are you waiting for?

58:13.210 --> 58:14.510
Do your job.

58:14.840 --> 58:17.750
Please let him die! Please.

58:21.940 --> 58:23.880
You took an oath!

58:24.740 --> 58:27.080
Don't take that chance waiting to kill that bitch!

58:35.770 --> 58:37.540
I shouldn't save him.

58:39.640 --> 58:40.950
I should let him die.

58:41.780 --> 58:43.200
If I save him,

58:44.150 --> 58:46.740
it might end up killing more people in the end.

58:47.930 --> 58:49.000
Save him.

58:50.220 --> 58:52.170
Do what you have to do as a doctor.

58:54.410 --> 58:55.930
If we have to kill him...

58:59.320 --> 59:03.120
I'll do my job and kill him.

59:45.640 --> 59:48.800
Next Episode

59:48.800 --> 59:49.940
There's no one here.

59:50.310 --> 59:51.520
The entire village is empty.

59:51.520 --> 59:53.980
This mission isn't about justice. It's about politics.

59:53.980 --> 59:55.970
We have a package from Shin Ji Yeong.

59:55.970 --> 59:57.250
Where are you now?

59:57.250 --> 59:58.490
This is a medicine cabinet.

59:58.490 --> 59:59.330
We're in trouble.

59:59.330 --> 01:00:01.070
If I don't come out in five minutes,

01:00:01.070 --> 01:00:02.380
go without me.

01:00:02.650 --> 01:00:04.720
That body was Mr. Jin.

01:00:04.720 --> 01:00:07.670
It looks like pernicious pestilence caused by the M type virus.

01:00:07.960 --> 01:00:08.970
Everyone! Stop!

01:00:08.970 --> 01:00:11.560
Step back from the operating table. Now!
